abstract: Three senators of the ruling anti-establishment 5-Star Movement quit the party on Thursday to join the far-right League opposition group, cutting the government’s already slim majority in the upper-house of parliament.
snippet: Three senators of the ruling anti-establishment 5-Star Movement quit the party on Thursday to join the far-right League opposition group, cutting the government’s already slim majority in the upper-house of parliament.
lead_paragraph: ROME — Three senators of the ruling anti-establishment 5-Star Movement quit the party on Thursday to join the far-right League opposition group, cutting the government’s already slim majority in the upper-house of parliament.
headline_main: Italy's Coalition Loses Three Senators in Blow to Already Tiny Majority
headline_print_headline: Italy's Coalition Loses Three Senators in Blow to Already Tiny Majority

abstract: Public testimony in Congress has done little to sway Wisconsin voters' views on the possible impeachment of President Donald Trump, a new poll from the battleground state showed on Thursday.
snippet: Public testimony in Congress has done little to sway Wisconsin voters' views on the possible impeachment of President Donald Trump, a new poll from the battleground state showed on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: DETROIT — Public testimony in Congress has done little to sway Wisconsin voters' views on the possible impeachment of President Donald Trump, a new poll from the battleground state showed on Thursday.
headline_main: Poll Shows Impeachment Hearings Had Little Sway on Wisconsin Voters
headline_print_headline: Poll Shows Impeachment Hearings Had Little Sway on Wisconsin Voters

abstract: The president’s concern is not so much whom he will be debating but the commission that runs the debates.
snippet: The president’s concern is not so much whom he will be debating but the commission that runs the debates.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump is discussing with his advisers the possibility of sitting out the general election debates in 2020 because of his misgivings about the commission that oversees them, according to two people familiar with the discussions.

abstract: As anti-government demonstrations engulfed Hong Kong in August, Reuters broke a sensitive story: Beijing had rejected a secret proposal by city leader Carrie Lam to meet several of the protesters’ demands in a bid to defuse the unrest.
snippet: As anti-government demonstrations engulfed Hong Kong in August, Reuters broke a sensitive story: Beijing had rejected a secret proposal by city leader Carrie Lam to meet several of the protesters’ demands in a bid to defuse the unrest.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — As anti-government demonstrations engulfed Hong Kong in August, Reuters broke a sensitive story: Beijing had rejected a secret proposal by city leader Carrie Lam to meet several of the protesters’ demands in a bid to defuse the unrest.
headline_main: Refinitiv Created Filter to Block Reuters Stories Amid Hong Kong Protests
headline_print_headline: Refinitiv Created Filter to Block Reuters Stories Amid Hong Kong Protests

abstract: Republican climate denial is even scarier than Trumpism.
snippet: Republican climate denial is even scarier than Trumpism.
lead_paragraph: The most terrifying aspect of the U.S. political drama isn’t the revelation that the president has abused his power for personal gain. If you didn’t see that coming from the day Donald Trump was elected, you weren’t paying attention.

abstract: House Democrats clashed with Education Secretary Betsy DeVos in a Thursday hearing that nearly spun out of control when one lawmaker called DeVos “the most unpopular person in our government" and said she's “out to destroy public education.”

lead_paragraph: House Democrats clashed with Education Secretary Betsy DeVos in a Thursday hearing that nearly spun out of control when one lawmaker called DeVos “the most unpopular person in our government" and said she's “out to destroy public education.”
headline_main: Democrats, DeVos Clash in Fiery Hearing That Turned Personal

abstract: Liberal activists have dogged Mr. Buttigieg’s high-dollar fund-raisers with calls of “Wall Street Pete,” in a sign of bubbling frustration with his candidacy.
snippet: Liberal activists have dogged Mr. Buttigieg’s high-dollar fund-raisers with calls of “Wall Street Pete,” in a sign of bubbling frustration with his candidacy.
lead_paragraph: Mayor Pete Buttigieg of South Bend, Ind., faced back-to-back days of protest this week, as liberal activists dogged his high-dollar fund-raisers with calls of “Wall Street Pete,” amid a growing effort by progressives to try to halt his momentum in the Iowa and New Hampshire nominating contests.

abstract: A Drawing Center show makes a soulful statement about the nature of creative expression and what it means to be imprisoned.
snippet: A Drawing Center show makes a soulful statement about the nature of creative expression and what it means to be imprisoned.
lead_paragraph: In the opening of her new book, “Making Comics,” the cartoonist and MacArthur fellow Lynda Barry reminds her adult readers that they made art when they were young, even if they self-consciously stopped doing so long ago. “There was a time when drawing and writing were not separated for you,” she writes. “We draw before we are taught.”

abstract: Mistakenly believing that a 16-year-old had fired on them, a mob of antigovernment protesters stabbed him to death.
snippet: Mistakenly believing that a 16-year-old had fired on them, a mob of antigovernment protesters stabbed him to death.
lead_paragraph: BAGHDAD — The antigovernment protests that have shaken Iraq for months took a brutal turn on Thursday when protesters lynched a 16-year-old boy who had fired a pistol in the air to try to shoo them away from his family’s home.
